   Up Arrow to Map   1. Lewis River - Island (WDFW)

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            30 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 4.8 mi; R at entrance sign to enter
        access site.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a few broken planks and exposed fasteners and
        rebar. The left side of the ramp is becoming undermined by the river
        current. No designated disabled parking. No overnight parking or
        camping.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Lewis River - Haapa Road (WDFW)

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager:
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on NE Hayes Rd (County Rd 16) 5.8 mi; NE on Etna Rd
        .2 mi; N on Haapa Rd to end of Rd.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is composed of loose gravel and small rock. The
        surface is uneven due to vehicles spinning tires. River current
        could be creating a hole at the ramp area. No overnight parking or
        camping. No designated disabled parking. An abandoned car has been
        dumped at the east end of the parking area.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. Cedar Creek - Pigeon Springs (WDFW)

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland E on Hayes Rd (County Rd 16) 8 mi; L at NE Etna Rd; go
        1.1 mi; access site on L just before Cedar Creek bridge.
        Site Description:

        The ramps are gentle to moderate in grade in a slow to moderate
        river current. The left ramp is in fair condition with only some
        slight undermining erosion. The right ramp is complete unusable
        because of severe undermining. There is a third ramp at the west end
        of the parking area. which appears to be in good condition, but has
        been blocked off by large boulders placed in front of the ramp. This
        site, located across the river from the Lewis River Hatchery, is a
        popular bank fishing spot. The parking lot is very rough. No
        designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Martin (WDFW) - Lewis River

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Take Exit 21 from I-5; go W on Davidson St.; L (south) on S Pekins
        Rd; follow to end of Rd.
        Site Description:

        This is a gentle to moderate grade ramp on a slow section of the
        Lewis River. Some of the steel fasteners are exposed and undermining
        erosion is occurring on the left side. No designated disabled
        parking. No overnight parking or camping at this site.


   Up Arrow to Map   5. Paradise Point State Park

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager: State Parks
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     19 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            7 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - park has designated summer and winter hours.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From La Center, W on NW La Center Rd 2 mi to I-5; N on I-5 2 mi;
        follow signs to Paradise Point State Park.
        Site Description:

        Paradise Point State Park also has picnic tables, BBQ grills,
        campsites, and a public phone. This boat ramp is located on a swift
        section of the river, but this should not affect launching too much
        because the gravel is tightly packed and protected from the sides.


   Up Arrow to Map   6. C.D. Hale Road Ramp - Lewis River

        Waterbody: East Fork - Lewis River
        Site Manager:
        Nearest City: Woodland


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Asphalt Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            12 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high water levels during flooding will prevent use of the
        ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Exit 16 on I-5, W on NW 319th St (becomes NW 41st Ave) .75
        mile; At 90 degree left turn, go straight on 41st Ave .5 mile; Turn
        L on C.D. Hale Rd; go .2 mile downhill on gravel Rd to parking area
        Site Description:

        The ramp grade is steep and drops off significantly after a few feet
        into the water. The ramp is asphalt, but has been heavily silted in
        so that the ramp surface is sand and silt. Drainage from the parking
        area has caused large ruts in the ramp. Boats can only access the
        left side of the boat ramp. No designated disabled parking.


