   Up Arrow to Map   8. Daybreak Park and Boat Launch

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager: Clark County Parks Dept
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            31 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Battleground, W on Heritage Loop Rd (SR 502) 3 mi. N on NE 72nd
        Ave 2.5 mi. boat launch is on E side of St.
        Site Description:

        There are two accessible picnic tables near the boat ramp area.
        Picnic tables are not accessible, however. Additional parking and
        play equipment are located across the street.


   Up Arrow to Map   9. Lewisville Park

        Waterbody: East Fork - Lewis River
        Site Manager: Clark County Parks Dept
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     4 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            4 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Battleground, W .5 mi on SR 502; N on SR 503 2.5 mi. park is on
        E side of St.
        Site Description:

        The gravel on the ramp is being washed away by river current.
        Lewisville Park is a large park that offers campsites, play
        equipment, ballfields, several picnic shelters, tennis courts, and a
        public phone.


   Up Arrow to Map   10. Columbia River - Shillapoo (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Columbia River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City: Vancouver


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     2 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            7 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        North of Vancouver on Lower River (SR 501) Road. Located on the
        Columbia River between SR 50l & Caterpiller Island.
        Site Description:

        The left side of the boat ramp is eroded and steel fasteners are
        exposed and corroding. No overnight parking or camping. Additional
        parking and restrooms are located across the road from the boat
        ramp.


   Up Arrow to Map   11. Vancouver Lake

        Waterbody: Vancouver Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City: Vancouver


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                               Boat Launch Type:

                                 1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     1 Paved and Striped Spaces

                               Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                 10 Gravel Spaces
                                 40 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        from I-5 in Vanvouver, exit interstate; go W on SR501 (W Fourth
        Plain Blvd); Go N on Fruit Valley Rd; Go W on La Frambois Rd to it
        end. boat ramp is 500 ft to W of paved parking lot.
        Site Description:

        The lake level was too high at the time of the site visit to
        distinguish the type of ramp and assess the ramp condition. The boat
        ramp is one component of the larger WDFW complex that offers various
        hunting opportunities.


   Up Arrow to Map   12. Marine Park (Vancouver)

        Waterbody: Columbia River
        Site Manager: Vancouver Parks & Rec Dept
        Nearest City: Vancouver


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  4 Asphalt Ramp
                                  2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     25 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  30 Paved Spaces, No Striping

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        E on SR14 from Vancouver, take first exit. S on Columbia Shores
        Blvd. E 1 mi on SE Columbia Parkway, R on Marine Park Drive; follow
        to launch.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is in good condition with a gentle grade. Marine Park
        is a large park with play equipment, picnic benches, picnic tables,
        and public phones. The boat ramp area is approximately .3 mile away
        from the main park.


