   Up Arrow to Map   14. Port of Camas - Washougal

        Waterbody: Columbia River
        Site Manager: Camas-Washougal Port of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Dumpstation
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  4 Asphalt Ramp
                                  4 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     42 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  32 Paved Spaces, No Striping

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Washougal, go W on SR 14, 1.5 mi; S .1 mi on Front St. E .1 mi
        on 2nd St. boat launch is behind Port Office Building.
        Site Description:

        A fee is charged for the use of the boat launch. This site also
        offers a lawn area, gazebo, picnic tables, and public phone.
        Restrooms are located in the back of the building on the lower
        floor.


   Up Arrow to Map   15. Hathaway Park

        Waterbody: Washougal River
        Site Manager: Washougal Parks Department
        Nearest City: Washougal


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces
                            1 Paved Spaces, No Striping

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Exit SR 14 at 15th St in Washougal, go N .25 mi; E on "E" St 8
        blocks; N on 25th St 3 blocks to entrance of Hathaway Park.
        Site Description:

        This boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located on a section of
        the river with moderate current. The ramp has broken planks and
        exposed steel fasteners and rebar. The upstream side is protected by
        rip-rap and a concrete wall. Hathaway Park also offers softball
        field & soccer fields, tennis courts, picnic tables, large lawn
        areas, paved trails, 2 playgrounds, and park benches. Additional
        parking can be found at the upper parking lot at the southern end of
        the park.


   Up Arrow to Map   16. Washougal River - County Line (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Washougal River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may affect the use of this ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From traffic light in Washougal, NE on SR 140, 8.5 mi to access Rd;
        Turn R; go 500 ft. to parking area.
        Site Description:

        This boat ramp has a moderate grade and is in a moderate to swift
        river current. There is an abrupt edge at the beginning of the ramp
        and significant undermining erosion at the bottom 10 feet of the
        ramp. The vault toilets are the "round" fiberglass units. No
        overnight parking or camping. No designated disabled parking. Wheel
        stops prevent a trailer from getting any closer than 6 feet away
        from the water. WDFW crews are clearing an overgrown lot on the site
        to provide more parking.



